                 <h3>Fish in the swishing waters</h3>
                 <p>
                     Sonamarg, a treasure trove of magical lakes, is the preferred spot among fishing and angling enthusiasts. Fly-fishing is particularly popular on the Indus River (also known as Sindh River), Krishnasar Lake, and Vishansar Lake.
                     Because the water bodies of Sonamarg are oxygen-rich, they are home to a diverse range of brown trout, snow trout, rainbow trout, Mahseer, and other fish. Trout and Mahseer schools can be found in the water bodies.
                     Although you can fish without permission in many places, you must acquire permission in others. The Directorate of Fisheries in Srinagar issues permits that allow for this for a maximum of three days. You can also rent equipment from this location. It's worth noting that the fishing season in Sonamarg runs from April to September.

                 </p>

